4b. Write a Python program to Demonstrate how to Draw a Scatter Plot 

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
hours = [5, 5.5, 6, 6.5, 7, 7.5, 8, 8.5, 9, 9.5, 16, 10.5, 11, 11.5, 12, 12.5, 13, 13.5, 14]
marks = [60, 62, 65, 66, 68, 70, 71, 68, 66, 65, 64, 62, 60, 58, 45, 43, 42, 40, 35]
plt.scatter(hours, marks)
plt.title("Hours to Marks Correlation")
plt.xlabel("Hours Studied")  # Clarified label
plt.ylabel("Marks Scored")
plt.show()


